commText: Sam Curran and Prabhsimran are at the crease. Sam Curran is on strike. Azmatullah will open the attack

Azmatullah to Sam Curran, no run, oh yorks him with an inswinger first up. Curran was late to bring the bat down, lucky it was just outside off stump and the ball escaped the bottom of the bat and rolled to the keeper
Azmatullah to Sam Curran, 1 run, full inswinger on the pads, Curran works it to mid-on and gets off the mark
Azmatullah to Prabhsimran, no run, swinging away from a length, Prabhsimran defends off the back foot
Azmatullah to Prabhsimran, no run, oh advances for a big slog, Azmatullah totally cramps him with a big inswinger in his attempt after a big shot on the leg-side, mistimed to mid-wicket
Azmatullah to Prabhsimran, no run, misses out on a glance as Azmatullah bowls an inswinger down leg
Azmatullah to Prabhsimran, 1 run, full and outside off stump, Prabhsimran leans into a lovely off-drive but mid-off cuts it off
Sandeep Warrier, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Warrier to Prabhsimran, FOUR, on the pads with no fine leg and it's a gift gleefully accepted by Prabhsimran. Length delivery down leg, Prabhsimran glances it ino the vacant region and gets four
Warrier to Prabhsimran, no run, oh tries to flick this short of length delivery behind square on the on-side, but ball bounces to hit him on the body
Warrier to Prabhsimran, no run, beaten! Length delivery outside off stump, Prabhsimran looks to drive and misses it completely
Warrier to Prabhsimran, 2 runs, drags this one through square leg and gets two
Warrier to Prabhsimran, FOUR, Prabhsimran advances and lofts this on the rise over wide mid-off. Short of a length delivery outside off stump, Prabhsimran puts on the bold face and hits it for four

Warrier to Prabhsimran, no ball, SIX, oh what was that? A high full toss above the waist. Prabhsimran was surprised on the charge but he managed to slice this slog over third man and it goes all the way. They check the height on that one it's a no ball with a free-hit to follow

Warrier to Prabhsimran, FOUR, now it's crashed through the off-side over cover. It's a 21-run run that swings the pendulum towards the PBKS very early. Poor length ball from Warrier and it got the treatment it deserved
Azmatullah to Sam Curran, FOUR, short of length delivery outside off stump, Curran uses the width on this one and cuts past point for four
Azmatullah to Sam Curran, 1 run, Curran sends this down to third man and gets Prabhsimran back on strike
Azmatullah to Prabhsimran, no run, Prabhsimran wants to continue in top gear. Advances but smart from Omarzai to drop this short with no room and it's a mishit towards mid-wicket

Azmatullah to Prabhsimran, SIX, whipped awayyyy! The attempted outswinger that doesn't swing. Prabhsimran sends it out of sight over backward square leg for a handsome six. Line was leg-side from short of length and he pounced
Azmatullah to Prabhsimran, no run, advances but Prabhsimran couldn't place this short of length delivery in the gap
Azmatullah to Prabhsimran, no run, slower delivery, Prabhsimran taps it towards point
Mohit Sharma, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Mohit Sharma to Sam Curran, FOUR, oh slashed and edgeddd! Saha doesn't have company to the left. He didn't react like keepers would do if first slip was there. Can't really blame him for not diving to the left, didn't look catchable and flew off the edge. Short of a length delivery, Curran escapes because Gill and Mohit didn't have a slip
Mohit Sharma to Sam Curran, no run, lovely bumper that forces Curran to duck

Mohit Sharma to Sam Curran, no run, he's still struggling for timing. Short of a length delivery outside off stump, Curran looks to push it through cover off the back foot, inside edge rolls to the on-side
Mohit Sharma to Sam Curran, wide, short and slow, Curran lets it go because it's too high
Mohit Sharma to Sam Curran, 1 run, short of length delivery, Curran mistimes the punch to mid-on. Change of angle for Mohit, went round the wicket for this one
STAT: This is just the third instance of Mohit Sharma bowling in the powerplay for GT, first this season.
Mohit Sharma to Prabhsimran, 1 run, length on the off stump, Prabhsimran taps it to cover for a smart single
Mohit Sharma to Sam Curran, 1 run, short of length delivery on the stumps, Curran works it to backward square leg
Rashid Khan, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Rashid Khan to Sam Curran, 1 run, googly on the stumps, Curran works it to mid-wicket
Rashid Khan to Prabhsimran, no run, oh backs away so early, Rashid Khan makes him fetch the cut, toe-ended to backward point
Rashid Khan to Prabhsimran, 1 run, neatly gets behind the line of this googly and taps it to short cover for a wise single
Rashid Khan to Sam Curran, no run, turning back and cramping Curran on the back foot punch, rushed shot to cover
Rashid Khan to Sam Curran, 1 run, on the leg stump, Curran works it to square leg
Rashid Khan to Prabhsimran, no run, short googly, Prabhsimran pulls well but Gill dives to the left and saves a certain four. Prabhsimran throws his head back in disappointment for missing out

Over Summary (1-5 ov) -- Azmatullah bowls a tight 1st over as he finds swing -- Prabhsimran goes after Warrier - 21 runs off the over -- Omarzai concedes 11 runs off his 2nd over -- Mohit bowls in the PP for the 1st time this season -- Rashid bowls an economical over
Wow, two overs of Mohit inside PP
Mohit Sharma to Sam Curran, 1 run, Curran swings hard, mistimes to mid-on

Mohit Sharma to Prabhsimran, SIX, how often do we see bowlers trying the short ball with width when third man and backward point is up! This is one that will irritate the coaches to the core. Prabhsimran gleefully stands tall and guides it over the third man fence
Mohit Sharma to Prabhsimran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mohit Sharma to Prabhsimran, out Caught by Saha!! Edgeddd and gone! Great comeback from Mohit Sharma and wisely he bowls the hard length with that field. Scrambled seam delivery that moved away off the pitch, Prabhsimran was down the pitch for a wild swing, thick edge with some bounce, great carry and Saha had to leap a bit to collect around head height to the right. Great grab that. But job well done by Prabhsimran. Prabhsimran c Saha b Mohit Sharma 35(21) [4s-3 6s-3]
Rilee Rossouw, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Mohit Sharma to Rossouw, FOUR, tries the wide yorker interestingly and Rossouw slices it over backward point. I'll take that offering first up says Rossouw and is off the mark with a four. Maybe he saw Bumrah nail him with the yorker last game and wanted to try the same but the line was too wide

STAT: This was just the second 50-plus opening partnership for PBKS this season after 102 (11.4 overs) between Shikhar Dhawan and Jonny Bairstow against LSG in Lucknow. Also the second 50-plus opening stand against GT this season, after 62 (5.2 overs) between Rachin Ravindra and Ruturaj Gaikwad in Chennai.
Mohit Sharma to Rossouw, no run, bowls into the wicket now, Rossouw lets it go. One bumper for the over says Rossouw
Mohit Sharma to Rossouw, no run, short of length delivery outside off stump, Rossouw punches it towards cover

Early timeout from the bowling side. PBKS are off to a good start. If they can pile up 190+ they have a great chance here. Curran tried his shots but didn't get the timing right but Prabhsimran had no such problems. PBKS have lost the most wickets in PP but they have countered that negative zone pretty well today, which is probably what forced the early timeout for GT because they were looking to take advantage of the early weakness from their opponents.
Noor on, watchout for the googly Rilee. Actually Sam Curran too. This guy is a good bowler to LHBs
Noor Ahmad, comes into the attack
Noor Ahmad to Sam Curran, 1 run, wanted to drive that through cover but sliced it through point
Noor Ahmad to Rossouw, 1 run, leggie outside off stump, Rossouw defends to coer-point and gets off strike
Slip in place for both batters
Noor Ahmad to Sam Curran, 1 run, there's the googly but it's too wide, toe-ended cut to point
Noor Ahmad to Rossouw, no run, oh almost chops it to the keeper/onto the stumps. Noor Ahmad gets closer to the stumps this time with the googly and Rossouw was troubled on the cut

Noor Ahmad to Rossouw, FOUR, Noor is trying to hide the ball on the off-side probably just because he has bigger boundary to play with than attack the stumps for wickets. Rossouw knows this and lines up for a reverse sweep, beats the dive at short third and gets four
Review for LBW. Was impact outside off? Ump's call will do for Rossouw. No bat on it. That's smashing middle and leg!
Noor Ahmad to Rossouw, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Noor Ahmad to Rossouw, out Lbw!! Very good review from GT. Looked pretty out but you can understand why the ump said no initially because it was a massive stride and then impact outside off could have come into picture. Noor Ahmad finally bowls the googly on the stumps and immediately gets his man. Big attempt for a slog-sweep from Rossouw, missed it completely, impact in line with off stump and that was always crashing into middle and leg. Noor Ahmad troubled Rossouw in SA20 and he's got his man here too. Rossouw lbw b Noor Ahmad 9(7) [4s-2]
Rashid Khan [1.0-0-3-0] is back into the attack
Jitesh Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Rashid Khan to Sam Curran, no run, Curran manages to work it to the off-side
Rashid Khan to Sam Curran, 1 run, pushed to long-on
Rashid Khan to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, flatter delivery, Jitesh works it to long-on
Rashid Khan to Sam Curran, 2 runs, goes back and cuts it to deep point, quickly gets back for the second too

Another appeal for LBW. If there was no bat Curran could be in trouble and they review after a deep discussion. Seemed like it did pitch in line. Or did it? No bat, ump doesn't even want UltraEdge because there's a gap between bat and ball. Gone!
Rashid Khan to Sam Curran, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Rashid Khan to Sam Curran, out Lbw!! Two very good reviews from GT and this should have really been given onfield. The leggie from Rashid Khan, Curran was across to flick this behind square, missed as he tried to play too square. It looked so out realtime with ball pitching in line with leg stump and it didn't turn too much. Spun just enough to smash the middle of leg stump. The Afghan spin-duo do their art again. PBKS have to rebuild again. Sam Curran lbw b Rashid Khan 20(19) [4s-2]
Liam Livingstone, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Rashid Khan to Livingstone, no run, big forward stride to defend this googly off the front foot
Noor Ahmad to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, googly but pitching outside leg, Jitesh nudges it to the on-side
Wow, they have a man under the lid at short leg
Noor Ahmad to Livingstone, 1 run, googly on the stumps, Livingstone flicks to deep square leg

The problem for Noor with his angle is that his googlies to RHBs have to be really full. But that's also the tease for both these batters. If they go across the line and miss that could be Noor's chance
Noor Ahmad to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, pushed away to point
Noor Ahmad to Livingstone, no run, and just like that! Another LBW appeal. it's a full googly but it's pitched outside leg and Livingstone escapes missing the sweep
Noor Ahmad to Livingstone, no run, defended to the off-side
Btw short leg moved to silly-point couple of balls earlier
Noor Ahmad to Livingstone, no run, beaten! Tries to play the googly but beaten on the angle
Rashid Khan to Jitesh Sharma, no run, googly on the off stump, nice forward stride to defend to cover
Rashid Khan to Jitesh Sharma, 2 runs, shortish delivery, Jitesh cuts to backward point, half stop with the dive and they get the extra run
Rashid Khan to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, leans into the off-drive and sends it to long-off
Rashid Khan to Livingstone, no run, oh inside edge saves Livingstone. Rushed on the back foot with a flat googly, would have been out plumb if not for bat
Rashid Khan to Livingstone, 1 run, slightly leg-sidish googly, driven to long-on
Rashid Khan to Jitesh Sharma, no run, turning away, read that off the pitch and managed to defend off the back foot

Over Summary (6-10 ov) - 29 runs | 3 wickets -- Fifty up in the 6th over -- SIX and OUT; Mohit nips out Prabhsimran -- Rossouw falls to Noor's googly -- 2 successful reviews from GT; Rashid traps Curran lbw -- No boundary for three overs

Noor Ahmad to Livingstone, FOUR, smart from Livi! He knows the googly has to be full from Noor, so he exposes the leg stump to trick the bowler into bowl close and full and easily scoops it to the fine leg fence
They move silly-point to short fine leg now to cover that off
Noor Ahmad to Livingstone, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Noor Ahmad to Livingstone, out Caught by Rahul Tewatia!! There's the revenge from Noor Ahmad. Googly angling across, Livingstone tries to flick too far behind square with a fairly big forward lunge, thick outside edge lobs and Tewatia moved to his right to accept the offer. Livingstone c Rahul Tewatia b Noor Ahmad 6(9) [4s-1]
Shashank Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Noor Ahmad to Shashank Singh, no run, moves across the stumps and defends this googly nicely
Noor Ahmad to Shashank Singh, 1 run, shortish delivery, Shashank goes back and punches it to deep cover
Noor Ahmad to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, googly on the stumps, Jitesh works it to long-on
Noor Ahmad to Shashank Singh, no run, full delivery outside off stump, Shashank drives to cover
Ravisrinivasan Sai Kishore, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack

Sai Kishore to Jitesh Sharma, SIX, what a brilliant hit from Jitesh. Lovely use of the feet to get to the pitch of the ball and the neatest of downswings through the line for a gorgeous lofted off-drive
Sai Kishore to Jitesh Sharma, no run, good from Sai Kishore to pull his length back and force Jitesh to lunge on the defence
Sai Kishore to Jitesh Sharma, no run, flatter and on the stumps, Jitesh pushes it back to the bowler
Sai Kishore to Jitesh Sharma, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Sai Kishore to Jitesh Sharma, out Bowled!! He owned him second ball after the six, then kept a lid on him next ball and now outsmarts Jitesh Sharma by slowing it up nicely and sucking Jitesh into a rash lofted shot. Oh he enjoyed that deception every bit. One of the finest left-arm spinners in the country currently. Jitesh jumped out of his crease and swung too hard, too early, ball looped, dipped and turned away from him to his top of leg stump. Jitesh Sharma b Sai Kishore 13(12) [6s-1]
Ashutosh Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Sai Kishore to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, forward defence
Sai Kishore to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, flatter delivery, Ashutosh defends. Outstanding over after the first ball six
It's again down to Shashank and Ashutosh. GT only have an over early left from both Noor and Rashid
Noor Ahmad to Shashank Singh, no run, flatter delivery, Shashank punches it to the off-side
Noor Ahmad to Shashank Singh, 1 run, full and down leg, Shashank mistimes the sweep to short fine leg
Noor Ahmad to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, wisely looks to defend this googly out
Noor Ahmad to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, this is goog maturity from Ashutosh Sharma to just play Noor out and only look to tap this full googly to long-on
Noor Ahmad to Shashank Singh, 1 run, Noor Ahmad keeps pushing it full hoping for a big hit but these two are playing him out nicely. Driven along the ground to long-off
Noor Ahmad to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, and again, just a nudge to long-on and that's Noor done for the day

Timeout from PBKS. It's down to these two yet again and full credit to them for playing Noor sensibly. Only one more over of Rashid to follow so they can counterattack. Sai Kishore will be an interesting battle though. PBKS had a great platform but the Afghan boys just spun a web to put the hosts a bit off track
PBKS top-five this season Inns: 8 Players used: 11 Runs: 744 Avg: 19.07 SR: 123.79 50s: 2 They have the lowest aggregate, average and strike-rate among the 10 teams.

Gujarat review! Sai Kishore and Saha were very confident with the LBW appeal. Gill wasted no time in sending it upstairs. Ashutosh is struck on the back pad. Is it sliding down leg? UltraEdge comes up with a flat line. Ball-tracking shows it to be missing. Not Out

Sai Kishore to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, Gujarat lose a review. They had been pretty good with their DRS usage until this point. The impact on the back pad might have played a roll. The arm-ball that drifts in, Ashutosh prods forward and is beaten on the inside edge, struck on the back pad and ball-tracking shows it to be missing leg-stump
Sai Kishore to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, flatter and sliding in, Ashutosh knocks it to mid-wicket
Sai Kishore to Shashank Singh, no run, slower and holds the length back, Shashank knocks it to cover

Sai Kishore to Shashank Singh, 1 run, in the air and safe. This is excellent bowling from Sai Kishore. He sees Shashank come down the track, so slows it up and holds the length back, Shashank is completely deceived as he goes through with the loft and miscues it over the bowler, the fielder from long-on comes in but can't get there in time
Sai Kishore to Ashutosh Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Sai Kishore to Ashutosh Sharma, out Caught by Mohit Sharma!! This time the ball carries to the fielder. No heroics from Ashutosh today. This pair has been separated early today. Once again Sai Kishore spots the shimmy down and floats the ball up outside off, Ashutosh is made to reach for the loft and the bottom hand comes off the bat handle, he mistimes it to deep extra cover where Mohit settles under and takes a good catch. Ashutosh Sharma c Mohit Sharma b Sai Kishore 3(8)
Punjab Kings have been forced to use their impact sub - Harpreet Bhatia comes in for Prabhsimran
Harpreet Singh Bhatia, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Sai Kishore to Harpreet Singh, 1 run, not much flight on this delivery, Harpreet drops it with soft hands to the off-side and opens his account
Rashid Khan [3.0-0-11-1] is back into the attack
Rashid Khan to Harpreet Singh, no run, googly and it turns away outside off, Harpreet stays back and is beaten on the outside edge
There's a slip in place
Rashid Khan to Harpreet Singh, no run, another wrong 'un around off, Harpreet blocks it to the off-side
Rashid Khan to Harpreet Singh, 1 run, googly outside off, Harpreet steers it past slip and backward point tidies up
Rashid Khan to Shashank Singh, 1 run, short of length googly. Shashank tucks it into the vacant mid-wicket region
Rashid Khan to Harpreet Singh, 1 run, wrong 'un close to off, Harpreet outside halves the block towards point
Rashid Khan to Shashank Singh, 1 run, flighted outside off, Shashank slices the drive through the empty backward point region. Rashid is done with the ball and he finishes with figures of 4-0-15-1

Over Summary (11-15 ov) - 23 runs | 3 wickets -- FOUR and OUT; Livingstone becomes Noor's 2nd victim -- Sai Kishore to Jitesh: 6 0 0 W -- Noor finishes with 4-0-20-2 -- GT lose a review challenging an lbw call against Ashutosh -- In-form Ashutosh falls to Sai Kishore -- Rashid Khan finishes with 4-0-15-1
Sai Kishore to Shashank Singh, 2 runs, flatter around off, Shashank nudges it to mid-wicket and Harpreet races back for the second
Sai Kishore to Shashank Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught&Bowled!!

Sai Kishore to Shashank Singh, out Caught&Bowled!! That's wicket no. 3 for Sai Kishore. Once again he deceives the batter in flight. Punjab in deep trouble now. Shashank steps out and does not get to the pitch, the ball dips on and he ends up chipping it back to the bowler, Sai Kishore bends forward and completes the catch. The GT spinners have been a strangle on this Punjab line-up. Shashank Singh c and b Sai Kishore 8(12)
Harpreet Brar, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Sai Kishore to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, slower and around off, Harpreet angles it to backward point
Sai Kishore to Harpreet Singh, 2 runs, clipped away wide of deep mid-wicket and the pair scamper back for the second
Sai Kishore to Harpreet Singh, 1 run, drifted across from round the wicket, Harpreet cuts it square and the sweeper tidies up
Sai Kishore to Harpreet Brar, FOUR, much needed for Punjab. Brar brings out the sweep and places it in front of square on the leg-side, right between deep square leg and deep mid-wicket
Shahrukh Khan, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
More spin coming up.. Now Shahrukh Khan given the ball. He had a very good TNPL with the ball. He bowls off-spin and is brought on for the two LHBs

Punjab review! Harpreet is given out LBW and he decides to challenge the onfield call. He had no other option but to use the review. Is this going down leg? UltraEdge shows no spike. Ball-tracking has it missing leg-stump. Not Out

Shahrukh Khan to Harpreet Singh, no run, Harpreet survives. Drifted across from round the wicket, Harpreet decides to play the sweeo first ball, misses and is struck on the pad. The impact was around leg-stump and the umpire was quick to raise his finger. But Harpreet gets it overturned thanks to the review - ball was missing leg-stump
Shahrukh Khan to Harpreet Singh, 1 run, comes down the track and mistimes the drive to long-on

Shahrukh Khan to Harpreet Brar, 2 runs, in the air and safe. Brar decides to take on Shahrukh and heaves it towards cow corner, does not get it anywhere close to the middle and the ball lands wide of long-on
STAT: Shahrukh Khan was the leading wicket-taker in TNPL 2023, with 17 wickets at 10.58 (ER: 6.66).
Shahrukh Khan to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, flatter and quicker, Brar punches it to long-off
Shahrukh Khan to Harpreet Singh, 2 runs, shimmies down and is cramped for room, nudges it to mid-wicket and picks up a couple
Shahrukh Khan to Harpreet Singh, 1 run, once more uses his feet and does not get to the pitch, settles with a drive to long-off
Looks like Sai Kishore won't finish his quota of overs.. Mohit is back
Mohit Sharma [2.0-0-19-1] is back into the attack
Mohit Sharma to Harpreet Singh, leg byes, 1 run, I0$ back of a length delivery, Harpreet is through the pull early and is struck on the back, the ball rolls towards point
Harpreet being attended to by the physio as he was hit around the ribcage. He seems to be fine and will continue

Mohit Sharma to Harpreet Brar, FOUR, Brar can bat. He picks the short of length delivery quickly, swivels and pulls it backward of square, one bounce and over the ropes. Few more hits and Punjab can get past that 140-mark

Mohit Sharma to Harpreet Brar, FOUR, back to back boundaries. Should Gill have continued with Sai Kishore? Slower back of the hand delivery, but dragged halfway down, Brar waits for it and swipes it in front of square on the leg-side
Mohit Sharma to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, I0$ short of length delivery, Brar mistimes the pull to deep mid-wicket
Mohit Sharma to Harpreet Singh, no run, I0$ good length ball and Harpreet creams it straight to extra cover
Mohit Sharma to Harpreet Singh, 1 run, off-cutter and Harpreet whips it to deep mid-wicket, retains strike
Gill has gone back to Sai Kishore..
Ravisrinivasan Sai Kishore [3.0-0-19-3] is back into the attack
Sai Kishore to Harpreet Singh, 1 run, angled outside off from round the wicket, Harpreet slices it to sweeper cover
Sai Kishore to Harpreet Brar, wide, tries to keep it out of Brar's range outside off and ends up firing it outside the marker

Sai Kishore to Harpreet Brar, 2 runs, dropped! This was regulation for Miller. Darted outside off, Brar reaches and slaps it towards long-off, Miller runs to his right and goes low to take the catch, he gets both hands but does not hang on
Sai Kishore to Harpreet Brar, no run, darted into the blockhole, Brar digs the drive back to Sai Kishore
Sai Kishore to Harpreet Brar, FOUR, one bounce and over the ropes. Brar drags it from outside off and nails the sweep in front of square, just wide of Rashid patrolling the deep mid-wicket fence
Sai Kishore to Harpreet Brar, SIX, this is turning out to be a good over for Punjab. Brar uses his feet and still has to fetch for the shot from outside off, he flat-bats it over the long-on fence
Sai Kishore to Harpreet Brar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Sai Kishore to Harpreet Brar, out Caught by Shahrukh Khan!! That's a well-judged catch by Shahrukh Khan. Sai Kishore finishes with a 4-fer - his best IPL figures. He bowls it fuller and almost near the yorker range, Brar manages to get under it but does not get it off the middle, Shahrukh times his jump to perfection near long-on and takes it over his head. Harpreet Brar c Shahrukh Khan b Sai Kishore 29(12) [4s-4 6s-1]
Gujarat Titans have made their impact sub - Warrier goes out and Sai Sudharsan comes in
Harshal Patel, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mohit Sharma to Harpreet Singh, 1 run, charges down and is met by a short of length delivery, pulled to long-on
Mohit Sharma to Harshal Patel, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mohit Sharma to Harshal Patel, out Caught by Shahrukh Khan!! Harshal perishes while trying to find the fence. Back of the hand slower ball and Harshal connected well, but does not get the elevation to clear long-on, Shahrukh takes a simpler catch compared to the last one. Four balls left and Punjab are 9 down.. Can they bat out their overs? Harshal Patel c Shahrukh Khan b Mohit Sharma 0(1)
Kagiso Rabada, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Mohit Sharma to Rabada, 1 run, slower ball outside off, Rabada chops it behind and Harpreet rushes for a quick single. A direct hit would have been close
Mohit Sharma to Harpreet Singh, no run, loopy full delivery outside off, Harpreet slices it over the point region and he's denied the single

Mohit Sharma to Harpreet Singh, no run, what is Harpreet thinking? Rabada can hit the long ball. But Harpreet is not giving him strike and misses out on two singles. Slower ball outside off and Harpreet pulls it to deep mid-wicket, single denied
Run-out check sent upstairs. Harpreet might be struggling. The bat is close to the line. The zoomer is being used. "The bat is outside the popping crease." says the third umpire. OUT
Mohit Sharma to Harpreet Singh, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Mohit Sharma to Harpreet Singh, out Harpreet Singh Run Out!! 1 run completed. That was a bizarre three balls from Harpreet, He struggled right through his stay and couldn't middle the ball but still denied singles to a capable Rabada. This was a slower ball and he drags it to deep square leg, races back for the second and puts the dive, but Saha's under-arm flick catches him just short of the crease. Harpreet Singh run out (Sai Sudharsan/Saha) 14(19)

21:18 Local Time, 15:48 GMT: Punjab Kings are definitely under par here and have not justified Sam Curran's decision to bat first. They got off to a good start - adding only their second 50+ opening stand of the season. Prabhsimran was motoring along but perished while playing the big shot, the spinners then came on and put a strangle once the powerplay was done. The spinners bowled 13 overs and returned with figures of 7/75. Sai Kishore being the pick of the bowlers with a 4-fer. Punjab crossed the 140-mark thanks to a cameo from Harpreet Brar, the spinning all-rounder struck a few boundaries to get them to a respectable total, while the other Harpreet struggled and wasted Punjab's impact sub card. The surface is slow and has help for the spinners. But Gujarat Titans should fancy chasing it down. Back soon..
PBKS innings progression Overs 1-6: 56/1 (RR: 9.33) Overs 7-15: 41/5 (RR: 4.55) Overs 16-20: 45/4 (RR: 9)
Pace vs spin in this innings \nPace: 2/66 from 7 overs (ER: 9.43) \nSpin: 7/75 from 13 overs (ER: 5.77)

-- 13 overs of spin is the most in an innings this season. It’s also the joint-most for GT in the IPL; Rashid Khan, Noor Ahmad, Jayant Yadav and Rahul Tewatia had returned 3/85 from 13 overs against LSG in Lucknow last year.

-- 7 wickets to spin is the most in an innings this season, bettering DC’s 5/125 from 10 overs against SRH from yesterday. It is also the most for GT in an innings, bettering 6/31 from 5.5 overs between Rashid Khan and R Sai Kishore against LSG in Pune in 2022.
